        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[Bassett, Southampton.]</placeName>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Absence from my home has prevented me from sooner acknowledging your letter May 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>., received yesterday Evening.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> The honour which the R. C of Physicians has conferred on me by the award of the Baly medal is a very great one, &amp; it is as deeply gratifying as it is surprising to me.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I hope to be able to attend on June 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> to receive the medal, but my health is very doubtful &amp; I may not be equal to the exertion. I will however, have the pleasure of communicating with you nearer to the time.</p>
<p>With my thanks for your obliging letter | I have the honour to remain | Sir | Your obdt servant | C. D</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Sir … C. D 3.1] <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 May] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘of [<hi rend="italic">below del</hi> ‘dated’]’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.2 yesterday] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘only’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.2 Evening] <hi rend="italic">above</hi> ‘Eg’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">1.3 it] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n6">0.1 Sir … C. D 3.1] <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi> </note>
            </div>
             
             
            
             
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter, the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12043.xml">letter from H. A. Pitman, 9 May 1879</ref>, and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12050.xml">letter to J. S. Burdon Sanderson, 13 May 1879</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12043.xml">letter from H. A. Pitman, 9 May 1879</ref>. Between 6 and 26 May 1879, the Darwins visited Worthing, Southampton, and Leith Hill Place; CD would have received Pitman’s letter in Southampton, where they stayed from 8 to 21 May (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">On the Baly medal, awarded biennially by the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4101.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal College of Physicians</ref> of London, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12043.xml">letter from H. A. Pitman, 9 May 1879</ref> and n. 1.</note>       
        </div>
    
